{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/2268/comments/33390103.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/2268/_/diff#comment-33390103"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 2268, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/2268.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/2268"}}, "title": "Add basic support for gnu precompiled headers"}, "content": {"raw": "Seems you've hardcoded some flags related to your specific build type.\n\nI changed these lines in `GazeboUtils.cmake` and now it works for me:\n\n\n```\n#!cmake\nset(FLAGS -fPIC -x c++-header)\n\nseparate_arguments(ARGS UNIX_COMMAND \"${CMAKE_C_FLAGS} ${CMAKE_CXX_FLAGS} ${ARGN}\")\n```", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Seems you've hardcoded some flags related to your specific build type.</p>\n<p>I changed these lines in <code>GazeboUtils.cmake</code> and now it works for me:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite language-cmake\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"nb\">set</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">FLAGS</span> <span class=\"s\">-fPIC</span> <span class=\"s\">-x</span> <span class=\"s\">c++-header</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"nb\">separate_arguments</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">ARGS</span> <span class=\"s\">UNIX_COMMAND</span> <span class=\"s2\">&quot;${CMAKE_C_FLAGS} ${CMAKE_CXX_FLAGS} ${ARGN}&quot;</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</pre></div>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-03-17T16:06:18.031991+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Martin Pecka", "uuid": "{41691c43-4ae0-49ba-ba45-3c36439f5af2}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B41691c43-4ae0-49ba-ba45-3c36439f5af2%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B41691c43-4ae0-49ba-ba45-3c36439f5af2%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/d1ad32a09564f856909994613fdbc37cd=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.n